<title>UK: Hanson plans Energy Group demerger Feb 24.</title>
<headline>Hanson plans Energy Group demerger Feb 24.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anglo-U.S. conglomerate Hanson Group said on Tuesday it would demerge its division The Energy Group Plc on February 24 if shareholders gave the go-ahead.</p>
<p>Hanson said an extraordinary general meeting would be held on February 21 in London to vote on the demerger proposal. It said shareholders would receive one share in the Energy Group for every 10 Hanson existing shares held.</p>
<p>Hanson said it expected dealing in Energy Group shares to start on February 24 in both London and New York.</p>
